        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 25 at 2:56PM PDT until September 25 at 3:30PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>SVRREV

The National Weather Service in Reno has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
West central Mineral County in western Nevada...

* Until 330 PM PDT.

* At 256 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Hawthorne, or
26 miles northeast of Bodie, moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Hawthorne, Mount Grant, Hawthorne Industrial Airport, and Fletcher.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Large hail, damaging wind, and continuous cloud to ground lightning
are occurring with this storm. Move indoors immediately. Lightning is
one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder,
you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
